A: You can use AsyncTask to parse your XML file and show a ProgressDialog. Here is a simple example:
private class ParseXMLTask extends AsyncTask<Void, Void, String[]> {

    ProgressDialog progressDialog;

    @Override
    protected void onPreExecute() {
        progressDialog = ProgressDialog.show(MainActivity.this, "", "Parsing...", true);
    }

    @Override
    protected String[] doInBackground(Void... params) {
        // Parse your XML file here
        // ...
        // Return the parsed data
        return parsedData;
    }

    @Override
    protected void onPostExecute(String[] result) {
        if (progressDialog.isShowing()) {
            progressDialog.dismiss();
        }

        // Use the parsed data here
        if (result[0].equals("steve")) {
            sayHiToSteve();
        }
    }
}

And then you can start the AsyncTask when your button is clicked:
public void onButtonClicked() {
    new ParseXMLTask().execute();
}

This way, the parsing of the XML file will be done in the background, not blocking the UI thread, and the ProgressDialog will be shown while the XML file is being parsed. Once the parsing is done, the ProgressDialog will be dismissed and the parsed data can be used in the onPostExecute() method.

